Collection of Kim Jong Il's Works Published in Kyrgyzstan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- The collection of leader   Kim Jong Il's works "For the Victory of the Cause of Socialism" was published by a publishing house of Kyrgyzstan.
 The book contains his works "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung," "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction," "Socialism Is a Science" and "Socialism Is What Keeps Our People Alive." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Klara Azhibekova, first secretary of the C. C., the Communist Party of Kyrgyzstan, at the book releasing ceremony held at the head office of its central committee on Sept. 27 praised the works of Kim Jong Il as important guidelines indicating the way for progressive humankind to follow. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Workers' Party of Korea founded by President Kim Il Sung has invariably covered the road of victory for the last six decades thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, a distinguished statesman, she added.

Monument to Revolutionary Activities of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Erected in Manpho City 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manpho, October 4 (KCNA) -- The monument to the revolutionary activities of President Kim Il Sung and leader
Kim Jong Il "May the giant footprints left by the leaders in Manpho shine" was erected in Manpho City, Jagang Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung conducted energetic activities in Manpho City to bring about a turning phase for the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War and devoted tireless efforts and wisdom to the work to turn the city into a land of bliss for people, a place good to work and live in. And Kim Jong Il has wisely led the work of the city true to the noble intention of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The natural granite monument is 10.8m long and 3.8m high. 
 Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, made an address at the unveiling ceremony of the monument held on the spot Tuesday.

Egyptian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hateer, Egyptian ambassador e. p. to the DPRK, Tuesday hosted a reception at the embassy here on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 The ambassador in his speech said that eternal President Kim Il Sung founded the WPK 60 years ago, ushering in a new era of freedom and happiness of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il is wisely leading the Korean people in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, he noted, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The peoples of both Egypt and the DPRK having long-standing cultures have made positive efforts to deepen the mutual understanding and develop the friendly relations.
 Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, in his speech said the foundation of the WPK by President Kim Il Sung was a historic event of fundamental significance in the Korean revolution and carving out the destiny of the Korean people.
 The WPK has grown strong to be the party of Kim Il Sung and a powerful political organization leading the Korean revolution to steady victory true to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Egyptian people have achieved great successes in the work for social and political stability and economic prosperity of the country under the leadership of President Mohamed Hosni Mubarak, he expressed the belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would develop more favorably thanks to their joint efforts.
 Present there on invitation were Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Kim Tang Su, director of the Bureau of Diplomatic Corps Affairs, and officials concerned.

National Seminar Held to Commemorate WPK Anniversary 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- A national seminar was held at the People's Palace of Culture Tuesday to commemorate the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Present there were Jong Ha Chol, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, Choe Ik Gyu, minister of Culture, and others.
 Presented at the seminar were papers under the titles "The foundation of the WPK was a historic event that set a shining example in building a revolutionary party in the era of Juche," "The idea and theory on building a Juche-oriented party serve as an undying great programme clearly indicating ways of building a working class revolutionary party," "The great undying leadership exploits performed in building the WPK into the party of the leader," "Developing the WPK into a mighty party steering the era of Songun provides a sure guarantee for accomplishing the Songun revolutionary cause," "The great leadership provided for building the WPK into the mother party looking after the people's destiny in a responsible manner" and "Let the whole party and  army and all people bring about a decisive turn in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation remaining loyal to the Songun idea and leadership of the great general." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floor was taken by Choe Chil Nam, editor-in-chief of Rodong Sinmun, Kim Si Hak, president of Kim Il Sung Higher Party School, Ri Thae Bong, editor-in-chief of Josoninmingun, Pak Jong Nam, secretary of the Kangwon Provincial Committee of the WPK, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers proved scientifically and theoretically in depth the immortal revolutionary exploits performed by Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il in the party building.
 Referring to the significance of the exploits performed in building a Juche-oriented party, they stressed that under the leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK has become a militant party which has modeled all members of the society on the Songun idea, taking it as steadfast guidelines in the party building and activities and won victory after victory in the drive to build a great prosperous powerful nation and in the confrontation with imperialism, with the U.S., putting forward the Korean People's Army as the main force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche-oriented idea and theory on party building formulated by Kim Jong Il as a perfect theory of the revolutionary party building in the era of independence serve as an undying grand programme for building a revolutionary party as they indicate the most correct ways of building the party into a political organization leading the work to materialize the leader's idea and establish his leadership, they said, and went on:
 By setting out the most scientific and revolutionary idea of party building in the era of Songun, Kim Jong Il provided a precious ideological and theoretical boon to steadily developing the WPK into a powerful political organization steering the Songun revolution despite whatever difficulties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the outstanding guidance of Kim Jong Il, who, regarding Songun as the warmest love for the people, has firmly protected the people's destiny with the Songun politics, the WPK has decisively met all the imperialists' challenges and frustrated their moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK, firmly defended the destiny of the country and the people and dynamically steered the building of a great prosperous powerful nation.

U.S. Urged to Drop Its Moves to Bring down DPRK system 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- The United States should clearly understand the inevitability of the failure of its Korea policy and abandon its ambition for bringing down the system in the DPRK, says Rodong Sinmun in a by-lined article today.
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is telling that it has no "intention to bring down the system of north Korea, while talking about "mutual respect" and "recognition of a sovereign state" at the place of talks, but behind the scene it is getting frantic in the war exercises and "human rights" offensive against the latter. This proves that the U.S. imperialists' moves to bring down the system of the DPRK are entering into an earnest and undisguised stage of action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is foolishly calculating that it can realize its ambition for "change of the system" in the DPRK with carrot and stick tactics. But it is seriously mistaken.
 It is a strategic error for the U.S. to try to carry out its ambition for the "change of the system" in the DPRK while trampling down on its sovereignty by force of arms.
 A war has not yet broken out in the Korean Peninsula despite the U.S. reckless military adventurous moves. This is because of the army and the people of the DPRK full of conviction of victory and strong fighting spirit to resolutely beat back the imperialists' aggression and eradicate the cause of war and the powerful military might of the DPRK built up under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are unfazed as they have the powerful military muscle to defend the cause of socialism and their destiny under the leadership of the illustrious commander born of Heaven. The might of the DPRK will be steadily strengthened and the anti-imperialist military front more firmly cemented as long as it is pursuing the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Any attempt to disarm the Korean people ideologically and bring down the system of the DPRK with "human rights" offensive and the strategy of undermining from within is as like as a daydream. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean-style socialism centred on the popular masses is genuine popular socialism chosen by the Korean people themselves and absolutely trusted and supported by them and herein lie the solidity and invincibility of Korean-style socialism. Steadfast and immutable are the Korean people's faith in socialism and will to defend the country.
 The single-minded unity of the leader, the party and the masses is the special feature which can be found only in Korean socialism. The unity is a patent weapon of the DPRK and it is more powerful than nuke. Anachronistic is the attempt of the U.S. to realize its ambition for bringing down the system of the DPRK by undermining and degenerating Korean socialism in which the leader, the party and the masses are united firmly.

Anniversary of WPK Celebrated in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- Colorful functions are taking place in the DPRK to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 An art performance was given by kindergarteners across the country at the Central Youth Hall on Oct. 4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was appreciated by Kim Yong Nam, Kim Il Chol, Choe Thae Bok, Choe Yong Rim, Kwak Pom Gi and Kim Yong Dae who is chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, Ryu Mi Yong who is chairperson of the Central Committee of the Chondoist Chongu Party, officials concerned and working people from all walks of life in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers put on the stage female chorus "Kindergarten is bosom of the mother, the Party", dance "Bell dance on holiday" and other colorful numbers, which vividly represented the bright appearance of the Korean children growing in happiness under the loving care of the benevolent Party which was founded by Generalissimo Kim Il Sung and is being led by General Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A celebration meeting was held by agricultural workers in the plaza of the Monument to Party Founding on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting a reporter and speakers called upon the agricultural workers to become the patriotic farmers in the Songun era and the farmer heroes in the 21st century who remain loyal to the Songun policy of the Party, give full play to the trait of aiding the army and uphold the Party and socialism with the increased grain production.
 Seminars were held at Kim Il Sung Higher Party School, the University of National Economics and Kum Song Political University on Oct. 1, 3 and 4. 
 Speakers said that the six-decade history of the WPK is the course of glory as it has successfully accomplished the cause of the building of the Party of Juche type and guided the revolution and construction to victory in storms of unprecedentedly complicated and rigorous revolution. They explained and proved that the WPK has performed the undying feats which will shine in the century under the banner of Juche, the banner of Songun.

Greetings to Kim Jong Il from Fidel Castro Ruz
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, received a message of greetings from Fidel Castro Ruz, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party, president of the Council of State and president of the Council of Ministers of Cuba, on October 2.
 The message reads: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I extend the sincerest congratulations to you and to the WPK and the DPRK government and people on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK.
 We will always remember the warm benevolence, support and solidarity to the Cuban people and the Cuban revolution sent by respected President Kim Il Sung, founder and leader of the WPK and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung, who devoted his all to the anti-imperialist struggle, the cause of socialism, the happiness of the people and national reunification, is always with us along with his exploits and historic last instructions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both Cuba and the DPRK could not but tide over the difficult and complicated situation owing to the changes in the international arena and the U.S. administration's intensified aggression and hostile acts in the last decade of the last century.
 The peoples of the two countries have steadily pushed forward socialist construction despite of big difficulties and, through it, demonstrated the might and vitality of their ideology and the unity of the revolutionary people and proved the importance of the decisive role of the CPC and the WPK, their vanguard units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Extending warm congratulations to you again on this significant holiday, I reaffirm our will to continuously strengthen the ties between the parties, governments and peoples of the two countries.
